FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1774612989
OL,3,CWales suffer World Cup heartbreak as
OL,4,Cdreams dashed on penalties
OL,6,FWales controlled the bulk of normal
OL,7,Ftime and led until the closing moments
OL,8,Fof the match thanks to a Daniel James
OL,9,Fwonder-strike. But Edin Dzeko's late
OL,10,Fequaliser sent the game into extra
OL,11,Ftime.
OL,13,FThe hosts pressed but couldn't find a
OL,14,Fwinner before disaster struck from the
OL,15,Fspot.
OL,17,FIt was the kind of night when an early
OL,18,Fgoal would light the fuse on a
OL,19,Fcrackling atmosphere. A stadium ready
OL,20,Fto explode in celebration.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/18
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1774612989
OL,3,CWales suffer World Cup heartbreak as
OL,4,Cdreams dashed on penalties
OL,6,FThat moment didn't arrive but the
OL,7,Frhythm of the game was established. It
OL,8,Fwas a real clash of styles as Wales
OL,9,Ffizzed the ball around with tempo and
OL,10,Fa more physical visiting side - they
OL,11,Fpicked up three yellow cards before
OL,12,Fhalf time - dropped into a defensive
OL,13,Fshape, happy to absorb and frustrate.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/18
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1774612989
OL,3,CWales suffer World Cup heartbreak as
OL,4,Cdreams dashed on penalties
OL,6,FIn the pre-match build-up Wales boss
OL,7,FCraig Bellamy promised 'full gas' from
OL,8,Fhis side and that mindset was evident
OL,9,Fin the way they harried and pressed in
OL,10,Fevery part of the field. But when they
OL,11,Fhad the ball, it was clear that
OL,12,FBellamy would have to delve into his
OL,13,Fbag of tactical tricks to unlock a
OL,14,Fwell-organised Bosnian defence.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/18
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1774612989
OL,3,CWales suffer World Cup heartbreak as
OL,4,Cdreams dashed on penalties
OL,6,FHarry Wilson, one of the form players
OL,7,Fin the Premier League, almost took
OL,8,Fmatters into his own hands when his
OL,9,Fcurling effort struck the inside of
OL,10,Fthe far post. It rebounded to safety
OL,11,Fbut it was the only moment of the
OL,12,Fopening half hour that threatened
OL,13,Feither goal.
OL,15,FTrue to Bellamy's prediction, Wales
OL,16,Fdominated possession but there was no
OL,17,Fway through. When the ground gave way
OL,18,Fas Daniel James prepared to unleash
OL,19,Ffrom long-range, it was clear this
OL,20,Fwould be a night that required
OL,21,Fpatience - or individual brilliance.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G5/18
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1774612989
OL,3,CWales suffer World Cup heartbreak as
OL,4,Cdreams dashed on penalties
OL,6,FAs Wales turned around to attack the
OL,7,FCanton Stand, that brilliance came
OL,8,Ffrom winger James.
OL,10,FA bobbling ball fell into his stride
OL,11,Fas he looked to get in behind. With
OL,12,Fdefenders closing in, he thrashed a
OL,13,Fhalf volley goalward from all of 35
OL,14,Fyards out. It caught Nikola Vasilj
OL,15,Fcompletely off-guard and sent Wales
OL,16,Finto the lead.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/18
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1774612989
OL,3,CWales suffer World Cup heartbreak as
OL,4,Cdreams dashed on penalties
OL,6,FJames' stunning strike would force
OL,7,FBosnia out of their shells. As they
OL,8,Fcommitted more men forward, Wales'
OL,9,Frapid attacking squadron of Wilson,
OL,10,FJames and Brennan Johnson were licking
OL,11,Ftheir lips.
OL,13,FThe Leeds winger almost doubled his
OL,14,Ftally immediately but his deflected
OL,15,Fshot spiralled onto the crossbar.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G7/18
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1774612989
OL,3,CWales suffer World Cup heartbreak as
OL,4,Cdreams dashed on penalties
OL,6,FThen came a reality check. With the
OL,7,Fvisitors committing men forward,
OL,8,Fsuddenly Wales had to defend more
OL,9,Furgently than they had all night. And
OL,10,Fwhen Edin Dzeko's nod back across goal
OL,11,Ffound his strike partner Ermedin
OL,12,FDemirovic, you were waiting for the
OL,13,Fnet to ripple.
OL,15,FBut the Bosnian's glancing header was
OL,16,Fstopped acrobatically by Darlow and
OL,17,Fthe stadium breathed a sigh of relief.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G8/18
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46109
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1774612989
OL,3,CWales suffer World Cup heartbreak as
OL,4,Cdreams dashed on penalties
OL,6,FAnd there were more nervy moments to
OL,7,Fcome. With 15 minutes to go, Joe Rodon
OL,8,Flet a cross go thinking it was sailing
OL,9,Fharmlessly to his goalkeeper. But
OL,10,FDemirovic had other ideas and was a
OL,11,Fwhisker away from latching onto it.
OL,13,FMoments later, Wilson's drilled effort
OL,14,Frose just over the bar and Johnson
OL,15,Fdragged another opportunity wide. It
OL,16,Fwas a game you simply couldn't take
OL,17,Fyour eyes off as it meandered into the
OL,18,Ffinal 10 minutes.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G9/18
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46110
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1774612989
OL,3,CWales suffer World Cup heartbreak as
OL,4,Cdreams dashed on penalties
OL,6,FAs the minutes ticked by, slower than
OL,7,Fthey usual do, Wales crept deeper and
OL,8,Fdeeper. The press was no longer
OL,9,Faggressive.
OL,11,FKerim Alajbegovic flashed a powerful
OL,12,Feffort dangerously close to Darlow's
OL,13,Fgoal. And then luck more than
OL,14,Fjudgement saw the Leeds 'keeper get in
OL,15,Fthe way of a deflected cross, forcing
OL,16,Fit behind for a corner. Six minutes of
OL,17,Fnormal time remained.
OL,19,FAmpadu thrashed a cut-back away to
OL,20,Fsafety. Five minutes of normal time
OL,21,Fremained.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G10/18
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46111
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1774612989
OL,3,CWales suffer World Cup heartbreak as
OL,4,Cdreams dashed on penalties
OL,6,FLiam Cullen, who may consider himself
OL,7,Flucky not to have received a red card
OL,8,Ffor leaving one on his opposite man,
OL,9,Fcleared a cross unconvincingly behind
OL,10,Ffor a corner. Four minutes of normal
OL,11,Ftime remained.
OL,13,FThe corner seemed to hang in the air
OL,14,Ffor an eternity as it headed for the
OL,15,Fmouth of Darlow's goal. And up rose
OL,16,Fthe evergreen Dzeko to nod it home.
OL,17,FThree minutes remained.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G11/18
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46112
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1774612989
OL,3,CWales suffer World Cup heartbreak as
OL,4,Cdreams dashed on penalties
OL,6,FAs the fourth official raised the
OL,7,Fboard to signal added time, the ball
OL,8,Fdropped to Cullen 10 yards out,
OL,9,Funmarked. But his stretched effort
OL,10,Fskewed wide of the target, capping a
OL,11,Fdifficult cameo for the Swansea
OL,12,Fmidfielder.
OL,14,FWhen the final whistle blew, a game
OL,15,Fthat Wales had completely controlled
OL,16,Fwas suddenly deadlocked. Extra time
OL,17,Floomed.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G12/18
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46113
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1774612989
OL,3,CWales suffer World Cup heartbreak as
OL,4,Cdreams dashed on penalties
OL,6,FBut the visitors carried the momentum.
OL,7,FWales' substitutes had struggled to
OL,8,Finfluence the game and those who had
OL,9,Fstarted looking jaded by their
OL,10,Fefforts. Bellamy's side would have to
OL,11,Fsummon something from deep.
OL,13,FThree minutes in, Mark Harris flicked
OL,14,Fthe ball to an unmarked Wilson, 12
OL,15,Fyards out. The rest was a foregone
OL,16,Fconclusion - until it wasn't.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G13/18
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46114
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1774612989
OL,3,CWales suffer World Cup heartbreak as
OL,4,Cdreams dashed on penalties
OL,6,FWilson had time to control the ball
OL,7,Fonto his left foot and pick his spot.
OL,8,FBut Tarik Muharemovic threw his head
OL,9,Fin the way of a ball that looked
OL,10,Fdestined for the top corner.
OL,12,FAs the first period of extra time drew
OL,13,Fto a close, Bosnia scrambled to stop
OL,14,FHarris flicking a cross toward the
OL,15,Fgoal and Ampadu's follow up was also
OL,16,Fblocked. After 105 minutes, nothing
OL,17,Fseparated the sides.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G14/18
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46115
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1774612989
OL,3,CWales suffer World Cup heartbreak as
OL,4,Cdreams dashed on penalties
OL,6,FThe second period of extra time
OL,7,Fdescended into chaos when referee
OL,8,FIstvan Kovacs refused to stop the game
OL,9,Fwhile Amar Dedic - still on his feet -
OL,10,Fcomplained of cramp.
OL,12,FDzeko, now replaced, raced into the
OL,13,FWales technical area gesticulating the
OL,14,Fthe officials as the home side won a
OL,15,Fcorner. The benches came together as
OL,16,Fvisiting manager Sergej Barbarez was
OL,17,Fbooked for clashing with a security
OL,18,Fguard. Meanwhile, the 40-year-old
OL,19,FDzeko gestured furiously towards
OL,20,FBellamy.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G15/18
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46116
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1774612989
OL,3,CWales suffer World Cup heartbreak as
OL,4,Cdreams dashed on penalties
OL,6,FWales wrestled back the ascendency.
OL,7,FSorba Thomas was causing havoc down
OL,8,Fthe left hand side, whipping cross
OL,9,Fafter cross into the middle. In added
OL,10,Ftime at the end of extra time, he
OL,11,Ffound Johnson at the back post. But
OL,12,Fhis header back across goal
OL,13,Fagonisingly evaded Harris and the game
OL,14,Fwould be decided by spot kicks.
OL,16,FUp first for the visitors was
OL,17,FDemirovic, who blasted it to Darlow's
OL,18,Fleft, but the Welshman got down well
OL,19,Fto save brilliantly. Next was Wilson,
OL,20,Fto the same corner. This time, the net
OL,21,Fbulged.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G16/18
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BWales News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,462,460,260,120,000,100
PN,46117
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F461A1774612989
OL,3,CWales suffer World Cup heartbreak as
OL,4,Cdreams dashed on penalties
OL,6,FThe teams went blow for blow until
OL,7,FBrennan Johnson put his effort over
OL,8,Fthe bar. After three penalties each,
OL,9,Fthe scores were level at 2-2.
OL,11,FAmir Hadziahmetovic found the top
OL,12,Fcorner and then Neco Williams was
OL,13,Fdenied by Vasilj. Suddenly, much like
OL,14,Fthe game in normal time, Wales had
OL,15,Flost control.
OL,17,FKerim Alajbegovic stepped up and
OL,18,Fconverted the crucial penalty, ending
OL,19,FWales' hopes of reaching the World Cup.
OL,26,@yD@Qrq
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                  G17/18
